                  <interp inst="t18201206-44-crimeloc278" type="placeName" value="Petticoat-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18201206-44-crimeloc278" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18201206-44-off276 t18201206-44-crimeloc278"></join>. On the 18th of November I let the prisoner a one pair back room, at No. 19, Petticoat-lane, which is in the City, at 4 s. 6 d. per week - he had a wife and three children - these things were let with it. On the 1st of December Kelly came to me I went and found his door open, and a candle and fire there - the things were gone. Next day I found him in custody with them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18201206-44-person464">
                  ANN 
                  KELLY
               <interp inst="t18201206-44-person464" type="surname" value="KELLY"></interp>
